                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi/Kolkata, May 12 : The price of tea has risen by 14.28 per cent to Rs 80 per kg at auction markets in the last two weeks. Retail prices have also risen by Rs 10 per kg in Chennai and Ahmedabad. According to official data, consumers in Chennai are paying the highest at Rs 240 per kg of loose tea followed by Shillong at Rs 200 per kg.                             
	 New Delhi, May 12: Ashok Leyland has signed an agreement with JBM Auto for setting up a manufacturing unit entailing an investment of Rs 100 crore at the companys upcoming plant in Uttarakhand. JBM Auto would hold 74 per cent stake in the joint venture.                             
	 New Delhi, May 12: Custom Excise amp; Service Tax Appellate Tribunal, has allowed Yamaha Motors appeal challenging the directions of excise officials to pay duty for the free after-sales-service offered by the company.                                                                                                                         
